{"id":"int-f86b2c19","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-16T14:28:10.974668738Z","actor":"Hans Kohlreiter","issue_id":"claude-dev-tools-8ry","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Deferred to v0.2 as part of the v0.1 simplification (see parent epic claude-dev-tools-yt7 and its design-change comment).\n\nOriginal scope: `/keep-awake on|off|status|gc` slash command depending on `force-on`/`force-off` helper verbs.\n\nFor v0.1, manual control is available directly via the `bin/keep-awake` helper (`keep-awake ping` / `keep-awake off` / `keep-awake status`) from any shell. The slash command provides ergonomic surface but is not required for the v0.1 use case.\n\nRevisit in v0.2 once the core plugin is shipping and we have a real signal on whether users actually want in-Claude manual control. If revived, recommend scoping down to status-only first (`/keep-awake` → `keep-awake status`) — see reviewer feedback on parent epic, finding S3.\n\n(--force used because the dependency edge to claude-dev-tools-8ed is stale: this issue is being closed due to scope deferral, not blocked completion.)\n"}}
